consensus_summary: FLAGGED FOR CONDITIONAL DEPLOYMENT - 22 SAST findings require review. Safe for controlled environments with security controls, but not ready for untrusted users without hardening.
key_findings: 22 SAST findings require comprehensive review and triage
Filesystem access represents inherent architectural risk
Can be safely deployed in controlled environments with appropriate security controls
Should not be exposed to untrusted users or networks without significant hardening
